ZH: 1. 讯号告诉我们火车即将到站。
EN: The signal informs us that the train is approaching the station.
ZH: 2. 我们需要一个可靠的讯号来指引我们的行动。
EN: We need a reliable signal to guide our actions.
ZH: 3. 这个机器会通过讯号发出警报。
EN: This machine will emit an alarm through a signal.
ZH: 4. 讯号显示我们失去了联系。
EN: The signal indicates that we lost communication.
ZH: 5. 警察通过讯号协调他们的行动。
EN: The police coordinate their actions through signals.
ZH: 6. 机器人通过讯号传达指令。
EN: The robot communicates instructions through signals.
ZH: 7. 讯号表明天气将会转晴。
EN: The signal indicates that the weather will clear up.
ZH: 8. 技术的进步使得讯号传输更加快速。
EN: Technological advancements have made signal transmission faster.
ZH: 9. 他们使用灯光讯号来进行沟通。
EN: They use light signals to communicate.
ZH: 10. 这个设备不再接收讯号。
EN: This device is no longer receiving signals.
ZH: 11. 讯号的丢失导致了通信中断。
EN: The loss of the signal resulted in a communication breakdown.
ZH: 12. 讯号的强度决定了通信质量。
EN: The strength of the signal determines the quality of communication.
ZH: 13. 我们需要一个稳定的讯号来确保顺利交流。
EN: We need a stable signal to ensure smooth communication.
ZH: 14. 军队使用代码解析讯号。
EN: The military uses codes to decipher signals.
ZH: 15. 电话讯号在传输过程中会受到干扰。
EN: Telephone signals can be interfered with during transmission.
ZH: 16. 通过讯号可以判断大脑的活动。
EN: Brain activity can be determined through signals.
ZH: 17. 长途车司机通过喇叭发出讯号。
EN: Long-distance bus drivers give signals through horns.
ZH: 18. 讯号指示我们走错了方向。
EN: The signal indicates that we took the wrong direction.
ZH: 19. 无线电讯号是远距离通信的重要方式。
EN: Radio signals are an essential means of long-distance communication.
ZH: 20. 我们需要一个明确的讯号来开始行动。
EN: We need a clear signal to start the action.
